briefdescription.para: Gets an object to manage the print areas of the worksheet.
Gets the first row that will repeat on the top of the printed pages.

detaileddescription.para: Use SetRowsToRepeatAtTop() to set the rows that will be repeated on the top of the printed pages.

briefdescription.para: Gets the last row that will repeat on the top of the printed pages.

detaileddescription.para: Use SetRowsToRepeatAtTop() to set the rows that will be repeated on the top of the printed pages.

briefdescription.para: Gets the first column to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

detaileddescription.para: The first column to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

briefdescription.para: Gets the last column to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

detaileddescription.para: The last column to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the page orientation for printing.

detaileddescription.para: The page orientation.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the number of pages wide (horizontal) the worksheet will be printed on.

detaileddescription.para: If you don't specify the PagesTall, Excel will adjust that value
based on the contents of the worksheet and the PagesWide number.
Setting this value will override the Scale value.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the number of pages tall (vertical) the worksheet will be printed on.

detaileddescription.para: If you don't specify the PagesWide, Excel will adjust that value
based on the contents of the worksheet and the PagesTall number.
Setting this value will override the Scale value.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the scale at which the worksheet will be printed.

detaileddescription.para: The worksheet will be printed on as many pages as necessary to print at the given scale.
Setting this value will override the PagesWide and PagesTall values.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the horizontal dpi for printing the worksheet.
Gets or sets the vertical dpi for printing the worksheet.
Gets or sets the page number that will begin the printout.

detaileddescription.para: For example, the first page of your printout could be numbered page 5.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the worksheet will be centered on the page horizontally.

detaileddescription.para: true if the worksheet will be centered on the page horizontally; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the worksheet will be centered on the page vertically.

detaileddescription.para: true if the worksheet will be centered on the page vartically; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the size of the paper to print the worksheet.
Gets an object to work with the page margins.
Gets an object to work with the page headers.
Gets an object to work with the page footers.
Gets or sets a value indicating whether Excel will automatically adjust the font size to the scale of the worksheet.

detaileddescription.para: true if Excel will automatically adjust the font size to the scale of the worksheet; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the header and footer margins are aligned with the left and right margins of the worksheet.

detaileddescription.para: true if the header and footer margins are aligned with the left and right margins of the worksheet; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the gridlines will be printed.

detaileddescription.para: true if the gridlines will be printed; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether to show row numbers and column letters/numbers.

detaileddescription.para: true to show row numbers and column letters/numbers; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the worksheet will be printed in black and white.

detaileddescription.para: true if the worksheet will be printed in black and white; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the worksheet will be printed in draft quality.

detaileddescription.para: true if the worksheet will be printed in draft quality; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the page order for printing.
Gets or sets how the comments will be printed.
Gets a list with the row breaks (for printing).
Gets a list with the column breaks (for printing).
Gets or sets how error values will be printed.
Sets the rows to repeat on the top of the printed pages.

parameterdescription.para: The range of rows to repeat on the top of the printed pages.

parameterdescription.para: The first row to repeat at top.
The last row to repeat at top.

briefdescription.para: Sets the rows to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

parameterdescription.para: The first column to repeat at left.
The last column to repeat at left.

briefdescription.para: Sets the rows to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

parameterdescription.para: The range of rows to repeat on the left of the printed pages.

briefdescription.para: Sets the scale at which the worksheet will be printed. This is equivalent to setting the Scale property.

detaileddescription.para: The worksheet will be printed on as many pages as necessary to print at the given scale.
Setting this value will override the PagesWide and PagesTall values.

parameterdescription.para: The scale at which the worksheet will be printed.

briefdescription.para: Gets or sets the number of pages the worksheet will be printed on.

detaileddescription.para: This is equivalent to setting both PagesWide and PagesTall properties.
Setting this value will override the Scale value.

briefdescription.para: Adds a horizontal page break after the given row.

parameterdescription.para: The row to insert the break.

briefdescription.para: Adds a vertical page break after the given column.

parameterdescription.para: The column to insert the break.
